In this article, President Obama discusses what he wrote in the guestbook at the Nobel Peace Prize signing ceremony. He wrote "Thank you" but also mentioned the importance of congratulating the Nobel Committee for their work in promoting peace and giving a voice to the voiceless and oppressed. He also highlights how winning the Nobel Prize had a galvanizing effect on Dr. King and increased his effectiveness in the United States. The President expresses gratitude for the legacy of the Nobel Committee.